    "template": "You are explaining an Entire Graph branch to a human reviewer. Analyze branch \"{{branch}}\" compared to \"{{base_branch}}\" and produce a concise semantic-diff narrative.\n\nInspect:\n1. git log origin/{{base_branch}}..HEAD --oneline\n2. git diff origin/{{base_branch}}...HEAD --stat\n3. git diff origin/{{base_branch}}...HEAD\n4. If the `entire graph` plugin is available without installing or downloading anything, run `entire graph diff --base origin/{{base_branch}} --head HEAD --json` and use it as supplementary evidence. If it is unavailable, continue from the Git diff.\n\nIdentify the important behavioral and architectural themes. Organize the branch into 1-5 ordered pages with 1-3 sections per page. Focus on provider contracts, CLI behavior, parser and relation changes, language-support changes, and performance or memory effects. Do not claim semantic impact that the evidence does not support.\n\nOutput ONLY this JSON object as the final line:\n\n{\"title\":\"<short title>\",\"summary\":\"<1-2 sentence branch summary>\",\"pages\":[{\"page_number\":1,\"title\":\"<page title>\",\"summary\":\"<page summary>\",\"sections\":[{\"title\":\"<section title>\",\"description\":\"<brief explanation>\",\"files\":[\"path/to/file.go\"]}]}]}\n\nThe JSON must be valid and match this schema exactly."
